." Manpage for ai
.TH ai 1 "February 2026" "setmy.info" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai \- print Markdown bullet lists from AI profiles and groups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ai
.I [PROFILE|GROUP]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B ai
command prints a Markdown bullet list composed from lines contained in
profile files and/or groups located under
.I $(smi-lib-location)/profiles/ai
on Linux systems.
.PP
Arguments can be either:
.IP \(bu 2
Profiles: files named
.I <name>.md
whose non-empty lines are printed prefixed with "- ".
.IP \(bu 2
Groups: files named
.I <name>.group
that contain a list of profile or group names. Groups are expanded
recursively, allowing groups to include other groups or profiles.
.PP
If an argument does not match a profile or a group, an error is printed to
stderr in the form:
.I "Profile or group not found: <name>"
.SH EXAMPLES
Print contents of two profiles:
.PP
.nf
ai java maven
.fi
.PP
Print a group (that expands to multiple profiles/groups) recursively:
.PP
.nf
ai tools
.fi
.PP
Combine a group with an extra profile:
.PP
.nf
ai tools node
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /opt/setmy.info/lib/profiles/ai/*.md
System-wide AI profile files (Markdown).
.TP
.I /opt/setmy.info/lib/profiles/ai/*.group
System-wide AI group definitions.
.TP
.I ~/.setmy.info/lib/ai (if used in future)
User overrides are not currently used by default, but the layout mirrors
system locations.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR term (1),
.BR smi-lib-location (1),
.BR ai-profiles-location (1)
